✅ What You'll Create:
A WordPress plugin that adds custom Elementor widgets, like:
-CTA Box
-Testimonial
-More in the future

🪜 Step-by-Step Guide to Create Elementor Custom Widgets Plugin

/wp-content/plugins/elementor-custom-widgets/
│
├── elementor-custom-widgets.php   ← Main plugin file
└── widgets/
    ├── cta-box-widget.php         ← First widget (CTA Box)
    └── testimonial-widget.php     ← Second widget (Testimonial Box)


🧩 Step 2: Create Main Plugin File
File: elementor-custom-widgets.php

✅ Purpose:
- Registers custom Elementor widgets
- Loads widget files
- Adds custom widget category in Elementor

Note: check file 1.1


🧱 Step 3: Create Your First Widget
File: widgets/cta-box-widget.php

✅ Purpose:
Creates a CTA box with customizable title, description, button, colors, padding.

Note: check file 1.2


💬 Step 4: Create Your Second Widget
File: widgets/testimonial-widget.php

✅ Purpose:
Displays a testimonial with image, name, and content.

Note: check file 1.3
